 Hunted (2003). This book, the first scholarly study of Friedkin’s films, reveals how they confront the ambiguities of law and morality, issues of subjectivity and problems of faith, while raising key questions around emotion and narrative in the cinema.Placing his work in the historical contexts of the Vietnam War and Nixon’s presidency, ReFocus: The Films of William Friedkin also examines the director’s representations of sex and violence after the dismantling of the Production Code and in light of the rise and fall of New Hollywood cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2021z9783110753790oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311078040640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147443139240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474431392423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474431392/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075403-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-078040-6  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-2